            <tr>
              <td colspan="6">
                <p class="ia-table-text"><b>What is the problem under consideration? Why is government intervention necessary?</b></p>
                <p class="ia-table-text">• Safety and Security (S&amp;S) declarations provide intelligence which is used by HMRC and Border Force to prevent illicit goods such as drugs and firearms entering and leaving the UK, and to tackle serious and organised crime and national security threats. </p>
                <p class="ia-table-text">• In August 2023, the previous government published a new model for importing goods into GB, and also announced that Entry Summary (ENS) declarations (a type of S&amp;S declaration for imports) would be required for EU imports into Great Britain (GB) from 31 October 2024. </p>
                <p class="ia-table-text">• The current government delayed introducing ENS declarations on EU imports to 31 January 2025, to ensure businesses have enough time to prepare for the new requirements. Businesses have been encouraged to start submitting declarations as soon as they are ready.</p>
                <p class="ia-table-text" />
